I"8<p>The methodology.  You’d think that once you’d done most of the work, it would be pretty easy to write.  After all, you’re writing about things you did.  It’s not like the sources section, where you have to read what other people have said about and done with the sources.  You can say ‘I did this, these were the problems, here’s a nice table’.  It’s the ‘these were the problems’ part, though, that is a massive pain.  It shows your research wasn’t perfect, because there’s no such thing as perfect research.  Research is messy.</p>
